### 1. Executive Summary
Paradox is a conversational AI recruitment platform founded in 2016 and headquartered in Scottsdale, Arizona [Will Chatbots Take Over HR Tech? Paradox Sets The Pace. – JOSH BERSIN](https://joshbersin.com/2024/04/will-chatbots-take-over-hr-tech-paradox-sets-the-pace/). The company reached $115.8 million in ARR in 2023 and was subsequently acquired by Workday for $1 billion in October 2025 [Paradox Revenue 2023: $115.8M ARR (Bootstrapped)](https://getlatka.com/companies/paradox.ai); [Workday completes acquisition of conversational AI firm Paradox | Staffing Industry Analysts](https://www.staffingindustry.com/editorial/it-staffing-report/workday-completes-acquisition-of-conversational-ai-firm-paradox). Paradox serves over 1,200 customers, primarily targeting high-volume hiring for global enterprises and mid-sized businesses across various industries [Paradox.ai - Market Share, Competitor Insights in Recruitment](https://6sense.com/tech/recruitment/paradoxandai-market-share); [Conversational hiring software that gets work done for you — Paradox](https://www.paradox.ai).

